p:::s27:::Drummond , who empathizes with Cates 's struggle and isolation , offers Cates the opportunity to change his plea on one condition : that Cates truly believes he has done wrong .
p:::s32:::Assuring her that Cates is fighting for a worthy cause , Drummond compliments Rachel on her strength in loving Cates .
p:::s47:::Drummond asks Howard if he believes what Cates taught him .
p:::s66:::The next day , just before the jury reads its verdict , Cates and Drummond discuss Cates 's chances .
p:::s80:::Word arrives that Brady has died of a `` busted belly , '' and Cates , Rachel , and Drummond decide to leave together on the train out of town that evening .
